From Peter Geltner Subject Re Soundblaster IRQ and Port settings In article Nicholas Vargish writes A SoundBlater SB card is supposed to share IRQ with parallel printer interface and in general this scheme works However sometimes there are conflicts it seemed to depend on the software more than anything Origin games are especially bitchy about having the WHOLE interrupt to My solution was to switch the interrupt to IRQ which is unreserved in contemporary computers using IRQ for the drives went out with the XT architechture DON'T put the SB in IRQ if you have an XT get a new computer instead This IRQ has been completely stable for me and I use my SB to play and under Linux a free UN X for or better PC architecture machines with no problems as well as games under I also use IRQ But there is one Some games assume that the board is using IRQ and have no way to adjust this I had trouble with some of the Lucas Films Peter Geltner Administrative Dean of Computing Santa Monica College Santa Monica California